{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ef4f99f9-c766-4150-8433-b9ccf3954b82","content":"Here's what I found in `my_app/`:\n\n### Untestable Static Dependencies\n\n| File | Line | Call | Risk |\n|------|------|------|------|\n| `views.py` | 3 | `datetime.now()` | Hard to control in tests — returns wall-clock time |\n\n**1 call site** found. It's a small project with just one file.\n\n### How to fix it (Python/Django)\n\nReplace `datetime.now()` with Django's `django.utils.timezone.now()`, then mock it in tests:\n\n```python\n# views.py\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\n```python\n# tests.py — freeze time easily\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\n@patch('my_app.views.timezone.now')\ndef test_index(self, mock_now):\n    mock_now.return_value = datetime(2026, 1, 1)\n    ...\n```\n\nAlternatively, the [`freezegun`](https://github.com/spulec/freezegun) library lets you freeze time with a decorator: `@freeze_time(\"2026-01-01\")`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8deec84b-4bd0-4360-b948-9da3388d1d55","outputTokens":306,"requestId":"1BD3:24177D:ACF205:C3C29B:6A03EE4A"},"id":"5a5b11a9-0258-49a7-a5c4-7e15f5636ea7","timestamp":"2026-05-13T03:21:53.509Z","parentId":"b68a2e20-d5ff-4482-ae91-814d934bcc00"}
